5 Classic Albums album for sale by Bob Marley / Bob Marley & The Wailers was released Nov 19, 2013 on the Island (Label) label. Island's 5 Classic Albums box set focuses on the latter half of iconic reggae singer Bob Marley's recording career, featuring his final studio albums: Rastaman Vibration (1976), Exodus (1977), Kaya (1978), Survival (1979), and Uprising (1980). Following his landmark Natty Dread album in 1974 and his hugely successful concert album Live! the following year, Bob Marley and his band the Wailers continued to produce vibrant, meaningful albums throughout the rest of the '70s, right up until the singer's untimely death in 1981. 5 Classic Albums CD music is a 5-disc set with 57 songs.
